I came across GetBufferData in [Index](https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Graphics/Vertices/IndexBuffer.OpenGL.cs#L77) and [VertexBuffer](https://github.com/mono/MonoGame/blob/develop/MonoGame.Framework/Graphics/Vertices/VertexBuffer.OpenGL.cs#L79) for OpenGL and noticed it's copying incorrectly.

```
byte[] buffer = data as byte[];
Marshal.Copy(ptr, buffer, 0, buffer.Length); 
```

should be

```
byte[] buffer = data as byte[];
Marshal.Copy(ptr, buffer, startIndex * elementSizeInByte, elementCount * elementSizeInByte);
```

right? Something similar is being done in VertexBuffer.OpenGL. This seems so obvious that it's a bit suspicious that it persisted in the codebase without anyone noticing, so that's why I'm double checking. If anyone can confirm I'll put up a PR.
